Arsenal have confirmed the signing of Leandro Trossard from Brighton. The two Premier League clubs agreed a £27m deal for the 28-year-old. Trossard completed his medicals with the Gunners today and was pictured in training with the rest of Mikel Arteta’s squad. Arsenal, in a statement on Friday, noted: “All documents have been submitted, we hope Leandro Trossard will be available for selection ahead of the match vs Manchester United.” Trossard, who can play across the front three, will wear the no. 19 shirt for Arsenal.